name: THE INTERSPINE
description:
1st Place winner of ACYA E-Sports Centre Design Challenge (Professional & Graduate Category)

Located at the KL Sports City – the new heart for sports and entertainment in Malaysia, this prototype building will celebrate the ever-increasing popular e-sports gaming while complimenting the existing physical sports and recreational facilities. Apart from the state-of-the-art digital arena, the various man-made landscapes created will attract the public to patronize the Sports City frequently.

The building is conceived as a series of roofscape with the intervention of sub-terranean underground facilities thus creating a seamless connection of existing nodes within the site. It also promises a clear view the National Stadium from the main carpark as one arrives at the KL Sports City.
